\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-16T19:02:36.689843+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"codex\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"duration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 489.157, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"event\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_pass\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"outcome\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"summary\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Task T-020@20260416T054258Z completed with outcome=success and verdict=PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"T-020@20260416T054258Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-16T19:11:00.623899+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"gemini\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"duration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 3104.134, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"event\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_pass\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"outcome\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"summary\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Task T-021@20260416T054258Z completed with outcome=success and verdict=PASS WITH NOTES.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"T-021@20260416T054258Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-16T20:03:07.350538+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"claude\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"duration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 477.768, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"event\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_pass\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"outcome\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"summary\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Task T-018@20260416T054258Za completed with outcome=success and verdict=PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"T-018@20260416T054258Za\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-16T20:13:00.719558+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndiff --git a/sdp/prd-snapshot.md b/sdp/prd-snapshot.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nindex 4ff5be6..16ccb8c 100644\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n--- a/sdp/prd-snapshot.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+++ b/sdp/prd-snapshot.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@@ -1,288 +1,163 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-# PRD Snapshot - PRD: CypherClaw Music Production Course Integration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Source:** `my-claw/sdp/prd-music-production-course.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**SHA-256:** `2ed4ef622028ccd47ff58a0ebf97bf53ad6c16901cc35550eaa31b8bdd359ca9`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Captured:** 2026-04-16T05:42:58.472655+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# PRD Snapshot - PRD: CypherClaw Humanization — Structured Expression Rendering Layer\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Source:** `my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**SHA-256:** `65bcff28a80825e9c3dd33ed94a39f17a86a9e5d3d4c81aa9c271db4fb9b06ba`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Captured:** 2026-04-16T18:19:25.336565+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n ---\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-# PRD: CypherClaw Music Production Course Integration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# PRD: CypherClaw Humanization — Structured Expression Rendering Layer\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n ## Overview\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-CypherClaw now has a working score-tree and tracker-based songwriting spine,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-but the musical education layer still needs to be encoded as software behavior.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-This PRD translates the CypherClaw Music Production Course into implementation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-work: theory, harmony, rhythm, synthesis, mixing, mastering, critical listening,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-SenseWeave interpretation, Theramini ensemble behavior, genre literacy, and\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-30-minute dramatic-arc production practice.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-The goal is not to store a static course document. The goal is to make the\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-course operational. CypherClaw should consult these ideas while composing,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-persist the resulting production choices in score trees and tracker metadata,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-verify them with tests/audio proxies, and use them during live playback.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-The production course is organized around the 30-minute dramatic arc:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Divination:** sparse listening, environmental responsiveness, wide space\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Emergence:** motifs and pulse forming, modal identity, opening filters\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Conversation:** dialogue, counterpoint, call-and-response, development\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Convergence:** density, climax, harmonic/rhythmic/timbral saturation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Crystallization:** resolution, reduction, memory, reverb tail, archive\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Every requirement below should make that arc more musically literate and more\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-verifiable.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Depends on:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/sdp/prd-songwriter-emsd-completion.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `docs/cypherclaw-score-tree-composition-spec.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `docs/cypherclaw-emsd-roadmap.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- current `ScoreTree`, composition gate, tracker compiler, tracker runtime,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  master bus, sample, self-listener, repertoire, and Theramini modules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Key files and modules:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/score_tree.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/recursive_composer.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/composition_gate.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/form_grammar.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/harmonic_planner.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/reharmonizer.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/hook_engine.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/tracker_compiler.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/music_tracker.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/music_tracker_runtime.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/arrangement_engine.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/mix_engine.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/master_bus.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/ear_engine.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sound_palette_lab.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sample_lab.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/dsp_scene_lab.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/theramini_duet.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/repertoire_memory.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/curriculum/EMSD-*`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- new production-course support modules under `my-claw/tools/senseweave/`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Current State Analysis\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Implemented Foundation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Score trees already represent commission, brief, form, motifs, sections,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  harmonic plan, arrangement plan, narrative map, and metadata.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- The composer can compile approved score trees into tracker scenes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- The runtime can schedule tracker rows, apply some row automation, and publish\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  current state.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Harmony, hooks, arrangement, mix, sound palette, sample, DSP, ear, and\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  repertoire helpers exist as first-pass modules.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- EMSD curriculum scaffolds exist and can be used as reference/curriculum\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  targets.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Remaining Production Gaps\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Pitch, scale, chord, voicing, and functional-harmony knowledge is scattered\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  and not consistently encoded in one verified musical vocabulary.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Rhythm currently uses duration cells, but not enough meter, swing,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  polyrhythm, phrase breath, metric modulation, or groove intent.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Counterpoint and motivic development exist only in partial metadata; they\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  need rules that can shape independent lanes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Synthesis, production, and mix choices are not yet explicitly selected from\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  the course concepts per arc phase.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Critical listening metrics exist as first-pass proxies but do not yet feed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  production choices strongly enough.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- SenseWeave mappings need musical interpretation rules for room, membrane,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  garden, Theramini, archive, and network sources.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Genre literacy is not yet a strategy library that can influence form,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  rhythm, harmony, sound design, and arrangement.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- The 30-minute production score needs to become a runtime phase profile,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  not only prose.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Goals\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Encode the course as a runtime production knowledge base with typed,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  testable concepts.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Make pitch, harmony, rhythm, counterpoint, synthesis, mix, and production\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  decisions visible in score-tree and tracker metadata.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Improve long-form musical variety without losing live safety.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Give each 30-minute arc phase a coherent production profile.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Make SenseWeave and Theramini inputs musically interpretable through course\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  concepts instead of arbitrary parameter mappings.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Add automated verification that catches unmusical regressions such as flat\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  loops, single-note drones, harsh registers, muddy mixes, missing transitions,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  and phase-inappropriate density.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Non-Goals\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Do not replace the existing score-tree/tracker runtime.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Do not require external music APIs or copyrighted training material.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Do not require real SuperCollider rendering for every unit test. Deterministic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  metadata tests and synthetic audio proxies are acceptable where live rendering\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  is impractical.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Do not make every piece complex. Divination and Crystallization may be sparse\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  by design, and micro pieces remain valid when complete.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Do not hardcode one style as CypherClaw's identity. Genre literacy should be\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  a strategy vocabulary, not an imitation machine.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Product Requirements\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| ID | Description | Priority | Tier | Acceptance Criteria |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-|---|---|---|---|---|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-001 | Create a production-course knowledge base that the composer can consult at runtime. | MUST | T1 | - course concepts are represented as typed data or markdown references with stable IDs<br/>- arc-phase profiles exist for Divination, Emergence, Conversation, Convergence, and Crystallization<br/>- tests verify all required chapters/phase profiles are present and loadable |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-002 | Implement a verified pitch, interval, scale, and mode library. | MUST | T1 | - library includes chromatic, major/minor, seven modes, pentatonic, whole-tone, octatonic, blues, Hirajoshi, In Sen, Pelog, Bhairav, Hungarian minor, Prometheus, and microtonal/ratio helpers<br/>- interval metadata includes semitones, consonance/dissonance, character, and arc-phase affinity<br/>- tests verify interval/scale pitch-class sets and MIDI/frequency conversion |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-003 | Add chord construction and voicing support. | MUST | T1 | - triads, seventh chords, extended chords, altered dominants, suspended/add chords, drop voicings, close/open voicings, and rootless/guide-tone voicings are supported<br/>- voicing engine respects register limits and configured spacing<br/>- tests verify chord pitch classes, unique voicings, range safety, and smooth voice-leading choices |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-004 | Encode functional harmony and modulation strategies. | MUST | T1 | - harmonic planner can label tonic, subdominant, dominant, secondary dominant, modal-interchange, tritone-sub, chromatic-mediant, pedal, planing, and modulation functions<br/>- score trees expose harmonic function and transition intent per section<br/>- tests verify cadence resolution, pivot/common-tone modulation continuity, and phase-appropriate tension levels |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-005 | Expand rhythm, meter, groove, and time handling. | MUST | T1 | - rhythm engine supports 4/4, 3/4, 6/8, 5/4, 7/8, free/rubato, swing, shuffle, dotted cells, push/pull, polyrhythm, polymeter, and metric modulation<br/>- tracker metadata carries meter, subdivision, swing ratio, groove timing, and phrase breath without breaking deterministic row scheduling<br/>- tests verify IOI ratios, swing offsets, polyrhythm cycle length, and phase-specific meter policies |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-006 | Add counterpoint and linear voice-combination rules. | MUST | T1 | - arrangement/compiler can choose contrary, oblique, parallel, echo, commentary, and completion relationships between lanes<br/>- dissonance and resolution rules are available as metadata checks<br/>- tests verify independent lane contours, staggered climaxes, and no accidental lane crowding |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-007 | Add post-tonal, spectral, and microtonal material strategies. | SHOULD | T2 | - composer can request pitch-class sets, spectral partial-derived harmony, just-intonation ratios, and 24-TET/ratio pitch events when phase/style permits<br/>- SenseWeave spectral analysis can seed harmonic material<br/>- tests verify generated material remains bounded and tagged as post-tonal/spectral/microtonal |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-008 | Build a synthesis-architecture strategy registry. | MUST | T1 | - registry covers subtractive, FM, additive, granular, physical modeling, and spectral/FFT processing with safe parameter ranges and arc-phase affinities<br/>- score tree or tracker scenes can request synthesis architecture by production role<br/>- tests verify each architecture has role tags, macro controls, safe ranges, and fallbacks |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-009 | Add production-aware frequency allocation and EQ policy. | MUST | T1 | - mix engine assigns sub, bass, low-mid, midrange, upper-mid, presence, and air lanes to roles<br/>- production metadata includes HPF/LPF/EQ intent for bass, pad, lead, texture, noise, sample, and Theramini lanes<br/>- tests verify role frequency lanes avoid primary masking and preserve bass center policy |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-010 | Add dynamics, compression, sidechain, and deference policy. | MUST | T1 | - production profile maps arc phase to dynamic range, compression intensity, transient policy, and sidechain/deference rules<br/>- Theramini and environmental transients can request generated-material ducking or silence<br/>- tests verify dynamic targets, sidechain metadata, and no over-compression in Divination/Crystallization |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-011 | Add spatial, reverb, and delay production profiles. | MUST | T1 | - phase profiles define stereo width, near/far depth, reverb size/decay/damping, delay style, and transition-space behavior<br/>- tracker scenes expose spatial intent and reverb/delay sends<br/>- tests verify wide sparse openings, clearer Conversation space, focused Convergence, and long Crystallization tails |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-012 | Complete mastering and loudness policy for installation playback. | MUST | T1 | - master policy targets installation-safe LUFS/peak ranges, limiter ceiling, broad EQ intent, and phase-specific dynamic contrast<br/>- automated proxies catch clipping, silence, harshness, and low-end runaway<br/>- tests verify master profiles and synthetic render/loudness proxies |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-013 | Implement critical-listening and psychoacoustic interpretation rules. | MUST | T1 | - ear engine or production evaluator exposes spectral balance, dynamic contour, spatial distribution, timbral quality, rhythmic activity, harmonic tension, masking risk, and equal-loudness compensation hints<br/>- feedback can modify future density, register, EQ, dynamics, and sound-palette choices<br/>- tests use synthetic events/audio features to verify correction decisions |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-014 | Encode SenseWeave voice-to-music interpretation rules. | MUST | T1 | - room, membrane/contact mic, garden, Theramini, archive, and network sources have musical mappings for pitch, rhythm, density, harmony, timbre, mix, and deference<br/>- Perform-VE condenser/room mic fallback is represented as a source option<br/>- tests verify quiet/noisy room, rain/wind/contact vibration, garden inactivity, Theramini activity, archive recall, and network/weather mappings |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-015 | Implement ensemble-space and Theramini partner behavior from the course. | MUST | T1 | - policy supports listening first, complementary register, rhythmic sympathy, harmonic response intervals, accompaniment textures, call/response, imitation, commentary, completion, and silence<br/>- score/tracker metadata identifies current lead/support roles<br/>- tests verify no register crowding, no excessive overlap during human/Theramini gesture, and recovery to solo mode |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-016 | Add a genre-literacy strategy library. | MUST | T1 | - strategies exist for ambient/drone/generative, minimalism, jazz, IDM/electronic, classical/orchestral form, musique concrete/electroacoustic, spectral music, blues, world-music concepts, and post-rock/experimental builds<br/>- strategies can influence form, harmony, rhythm, synthesis, arrangement, and mix without hardcoding imitation<br/>- tests verify strategy selection, arc affinity, and no missing required genre strategy |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-017 | Make the 30-minute production score executable. | MUST | T1 | - procedural arc exposes per-phase density, dynamic, harmonic, rhythm, timbre, spatial, compression, SenseWeave, and synthesis targets<br/>- score-tree commissioning and tracker compilation use those targets for long pieces and 5-minute proxy tests<br/>- tests verify the five-phase contour and phase-specific production metadata |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-018 | Add phase-transition composition techniques. | MUST | T1 | - transition planner supports pivot event, breath/silence, metric modulation, timbral morph, harmonic pivot chord, and common-tone bridge<br/>- adjacent sections share at least one continuity element unless a deliberate hard cut is tagged<br/>- tests verify no untagged abrupt phase jumps and valid transition metadata |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-019 | Build SuperCollider recipe references without coupling tests to live audio. | SHOULD | T2 | - reference recipes exist for MIDI-to-frequency, intervals, scales, chord voicings, swing, polyrhythm, subtractive, FM, additive, granular, physical modeling, spectral freeze, EQ, compression, sidechain, reverb, delay, master bus, groups, buses, patterns, and envelopes<br/>- recipes are discoverable from curriculum/reference docs<br/>- tests verify recipe files and required labels exist |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-020 | Wire production-course choices into score trees and tracker output. | MUST | T1 | - score trees carry production vocabulary for mode/scale, harmonic function, meter/groove, counterpoint relation, synthesis architecture, mix role, spatial intent, genre strategy, phase profile, and transition type<br/>- tracker scenes/steps preserve enough metadata for runtime scheduling and diagnostics<br/>- tests verify metadata survives compose -> gate -> compile -> schedule |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-021 | Extend the composition gate with production-course checks. | MUST | T1 | - gate can reject phase-inappropriate density, missing harmonic/rhythm metadata, unsafe register, flat dynamics, missing transition continuity, missing mix role, and untagged genre/strategy choices for long pieces<br/>- intentionally sparse/micro pieces can pass when they carry valid sparse intent<br/>- tests cover both rejection and acceptance paths |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-022 | Add course-driven self-critique and revision targets. | SHOULD | T2 | - critique output names concrete course concepts behind failures, such as masking, no recurrence, no cadence, weak transition, over-compression, or unsupported density<br/>- bounded revision can adjust form, harmony, rhythm, register, mix, or strategy without changing piece identity<br/>- tests verify at least one metric improves after revision |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-023 | Turn the production course into executable curriculum exercises. | SHOULD | T2 | - curriculum includes exercises/tests for intervals/scales, chord voicings, progressions, rhythm/groove, counterpoint, synthesis architecture, mix/master, SenseWeave mapping, Theramini ensemble, genre strategy, and full arc production<br/>- exercise metadata includes objective, template, verifier, and expected features<br/>- tests verify curriculum completeness and runnable verifier stubs |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-024 | Add operator diagnostics for production-course decisions. | SHOULD | T2 | - face/status/operator output can show current phase, scale/mode, harmonic function, groove, production strategy, mix role, spatial profile, SenseWeave source, Theramini relation, and critique notes<br/>- diagnostics degrade gracefully when data is absent<br/>- tests verify status payload shape and no hallucinated unavailable fields |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-025 | Add end-to-end production-course integration tests. | MUST | T1 | - tests compose, gate, compile, schedule, and inspect a 5-minute proxy arc using production-course metadata<br/>- tests verify non-silent output proxy, no single-note long sections, phase contour, transition continuity, mix role allocation, and repertoire storage<br/>- tests run without live hardware and with mocked SenseWeave/Theramini inputs |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Dependency Map\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-```text\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-001 -> MPC-002, MPC-008, MPC-017, MPC-019\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-002 -> MPC-003, MPC-004, MPC-007\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-003 -> MPC-004, MPC-006, MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-004 -> MPC-017, MPC-018, MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-005 -> MPC-006, MPC-017, MPC-018, MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-006 -> MPC-015, MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-007 -> MPC-008, MPC-014, MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-008 -> MPC-009, MPC-011, MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-009 -> MPC-010, MPC-012, MPC-021\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-010 -> MPC-012, MPC-015, MPC-021\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-011 -> MPC-017, MPC-018, MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-012 -> MPC-013, MPC-021\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-013 -> MPC-014, MPC-022\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-014 -> MPC-015, MPC-017, MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-015 -> MPC-020, MPC-025\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-016 -> MPC-017, MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-017 -> MPC-018, MPC-020, MPC-025\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-018 -> MPC-020, MPC-021\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-019 -> MPC-023\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-020 -> MPC-021, MPC-024, MPC-025\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-021 -> MPC-022, MPC-025\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-022 -> MPC-025\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-023 -> MPC-024\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-024 -> MPC-025\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Suggested Implementation Phases\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Phase 1: Musical Vocabulary Runtime\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Focus requirements:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-001\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-002\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-003\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-004\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-005\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Goal:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- establish verified pitch, harmony, chord, rhythm, and production-course data\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  that downstream modules can depend on.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Phase 2: Production Strategy and Arc Profiles\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Focus requirements:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-008\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-009\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-010\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-011\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-012\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-017\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-018\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Goal:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- make each arc phase produce coherent synthesis, mix, dynamics, space, and\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  transition decisions.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Phase 3: Listening, Environment, and Ensemble\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Focus requirements:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-006\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-007\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-013\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-014\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-015\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Goal:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- connect critical listening, SenseWeave, Theramini, counterpoint, and spectral\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  material to concrete score-tree and runtime choices.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Phase 4: Genre Literacy and Curriculum\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Focus requirements:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-016\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-019\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-023\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-024\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Goal:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- turn the course into reusable references, strategy libraries, exercises, and\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  operator-visible diagnostics.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Phase 5: Integration, Gate, and Revision\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Focus requirements:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-021\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-022\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-025\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Goal:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- prove the production-course layer survives the full compose -> gate ->\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  compile -> schedule -> critique -> store path.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Verification Strategy\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Unit tests for theory primitives: intervals, pitch classes, scales, modes,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  MIDI/frequency conversion, chord construction, voicing uniqueness, cadence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  labels, and rhythm IOI ratios.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Metadata tests for score-tree/tracker propagation: arc phase, production\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  strategy, synthesis architecture, mix role, spatial profile, transition type,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  genre strategy, and SenseWeave/Theramini relation.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Synthetic audio/proxy tests for mix/master: clipping, silence, harshness,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  low-end runaway, rough spectral balance, rough loudness target, and dynamic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  contour.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Integration tests for 5-minute proxy arcs, mocked SenseWeave streams,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  mocked Theramini activity, repertoire storage, and course-driven critique.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Curriculum tests that ensure references, recipes, prompts, exercises, and\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  verifier stubs remain present as the course expands.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Rollout Notes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Load this PRD after the current songwriter/EMSD completion PRD.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Keep the initial implementation behind the current fractal-form chain so it\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  does not interrupt T-014 through T-020.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Prefer metadata and deterministic proxy verification before adding expensive\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  live SuperCollider rendering.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Treat the production-course data as a compositional policy layer. Runtime\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  modules should be able to ignore unavailable inputs and fall back to safe\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  phase defaults.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+CypherClaw already composes legible music: score trees, section functions, production profiles, genre strategies, SenseWeave mappings. But the path from composed score to synthesized audio still renders too rigidly. Phrases don't breathe. Repeated motifs don't vary. Silence is a byproduct of scheduling rather than an intentional voice. Sensors occasionally read like one-to-one controllers rather than shaping aggregate intent. The result is the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"almost-human\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" failure mode: structurally competent, expressively flat.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The fix is not sprinkled randomness. The research literature is unambiguous on this: human expressive variance is **structured, not stochastic**. Random jitter is what produces the uncanny-valley failure, not what escapes it.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+This PRD installs a dedicated **rendering layer** — a compiler pass between composition (score-tree) and synthesis (SuperCollider) — that translates score structure into correlated, intentional deviations in timing, dynamics, articulation, and silence. The architecture is KTH-rule-system-style: a stack of ordered, pure-function rules, each reading score features and emitting event-level deviations, each toggleable and quantity-adjustable, each leaving provenance on every event so authors can ablate and debug.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+Five principles govern the whole design:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+1. **Structured over stochastic.** Every deviation is a function of score/sensor features. Gaussian jitter is allowed only below the listener JND (~3–5 ms, ~2 velocity units) and only as a final polish *on top of* intentional deviations.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+2. **Hierarchical arcs.** Section-level tempo elasticity modulates phrase-level arcs, which modulate note-level accents. Arcs compose multiplicatively.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+3. **Legible intent.** Every phrase declares an intent tag (build/settle/question/answer/withhold/punctuate). Parameters are chosen so the intent is perceptible.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+4. **Restraint as material.** Silence is scheduled, not residual. Density and silence budgets are maintained per voice and per section.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+5. **Machine identity preserved.** Grid-locked elements (ostinati, sequencers, polyrhythmic machines), superhuman precision, and alien timbres are deliberately *not* humanized. CypherClaw is a robot musician that has learned which things humans shape — not a robot pretending to be a violinist.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The goal is not realism. It is **legibility**: a listener should feel that CypherClaw *intended* each phrase — to build, to withhold, to answer the room.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Scope and non-goals\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**In scope:** a new rendering stage between composition and synthesis; an Event/PerformanceIntent/SectionEnvelope data model with rule-stack provenance; a 12-rule render stack (R1–R12); a seeded-RNG architecture with per-stage sub-seeds; a replay harness; a rule-ablation debugger; a metrics-CI gate with anti-pattern detection; a performance-worm diagnostic; a bounded sensor-to-intent aggregation matrix.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Out of scope / non-goals:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Photorealistic human-performance imitation. CypherClaw is a robot musician, not a violinist simulator.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- General-purpose MIDI humanizer — this is not a plugin.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Sensor-driven note generation. Sensors modulate expression, never replace composition.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Machine-learning performance models in this phase. Rule-based KTH-style is interpretable, debuggable, and gateable with fixed metrics. Learned models can be added after the metric gate is stable.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Replacement of existing composition, production-course, or synthesis work. This layer sits *above* synthesis and *below* composition — it renders what the composer emits.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## The four phases\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Phase 1 — Foundations (CCH-001..CCH-010).** Data model, seeded-RNG plumbing, replay harness, rule-ablation debugger. At end of phase, existing pieces render bit-identically through the new pipeline with no rules active — just plumbing.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Phase 2 — Core rule stack (CCH-011..CCH-021).** R1 Metric Accent, R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH parabolic), R3 Agogic Accent, R4 Duration Contrast, R5 Final Ritardando (Friberg–Sundberg square-root), R6 Punctuation+Breath, R7 Articulation Shaping, R8 Microtiming Polish (below JND). Role-filter gating so grid-locked voices skip the stack. Phrase-feature extraction via partitura. End-of-phase: single-voice melodic passages sound shaped, not flat; metric gate shows structured deviations vs. flat-line baseline.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Phase 3 — Memory, silence, ensemble (CCH-022..CCH-029).** R9 Motif memory with LRU + variation menu + return-home decay. R10 Silence budgets with wind-voice lung-capacity caps. R11 Call-response gating. Section-level envelope compositing. Tempo-dependent swing (Friberg/Sundström). Arc-shape variety. Restraint as global dampener. End-of-phase: 5-minute generative pieces no longer feel looped; repetition-variance metrics pass thresholds.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Phase 4 — Sensor aggregation + narrative coupling (CCH-030..CCH-033).** R12 Sensor-to-intent matrix (smoothed IIR, hysteresis, aggregate intentions — never one-to-one). Bounded reactive delta track. Narrative engine → SectionEnvelope coupling. End-of-phase: installation responds legibly to audience presence without gimmicky mappings.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Metrics-CI Gate + Diagnostics (CCH-034..CCH-040).** Metric battery, anti-pattern detection, performance-worm logger, CI integration, audio-rendered cross-check, provenance in exported audio metadata, listener-review workflow. Runs in parallel with rule-stack build-out; most checks land alongside the rule they validate.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Depends on\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `my-claw/sdp/prd-music-production-course.md` — the currently-executing PRD covering production profiles, harmonic library, SenseWeave mappings, genre strategies, phase transitions. Rules R1–R8 read phase profiles and harmonic-function metadata from that layer.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `docs/cypherclaw-score-tree-composition-spec.md` — the score-tree composer this layer renders from.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` — reference for existing musicianship vocabulary.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Current `ScoreTree`, composition gate, tracker compiler, tracker runtime, master bus, self-listener, Theramini modules.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Key files and modules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **New** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/` package:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/events.py` — Event, PerformanceIntent, SectionEnvelope, IntentTag, Role dataclasses\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/seed.py` — per-stage sub-seed derivation, replay harness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/rules/` — one module per R-rule (metric_accent.py, phrase_arch.py, agogic.py, duration_contrast.py, final_rit.py, punctuation.py, articulation.py, microtiming.py, motif_memory.py, silence_budget.py, call_response.py, sensor_intent.py)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/pass_.py` — RenderPass framework, ordered rule stack, ablation support\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/features.py` — partitura-backed phrase/harmonic feature extraction\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/replay.py` — bit-identical (score, seed, delta_track) → performed_part reproduction\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/worm.py` — performance-worm logger and convex-hull diagnostic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/metrics.py` — IOI CoV, velocity σ, DNVR, GS, pitch H1, LZ76, tempo autocorrelation, silence coverage\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/antipatterns.py` — quantization-ghosting, dynamic-compression, motif-ossification, random-as-expression, symmetric-arc-uncanny, dead-silence detectors\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/score_tree.py` — score-tree nodes carry PerformanceIntent / SectionEnvelope metadata\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/recursive_composer.py` — emits score-tree with new metadata; composition seed threaded through\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/composition_gate.py` — gate checks new metadata present on all phrases\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/music_tracker.py` / `music_tracker_runtime.py` — tracker scenes preserve Event metadata through compile → schedule\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/operator_diagnostics.py` — surface active rule stack, current phrase intent, worm snapshot\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **New** `my-claw/tests/test_render_*.py` — per-rule, role-filter, replay, ablation, metric, anti-pattern tests\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Requirements\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| ID | Description | Priority | Tier | Acceptance criteria |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+|----|-------------|----------|------|---------------------|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-001 | Implement the Event dataclass with score-level, performance-level, reactive-delta, and provenance fields. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines Event with event_id, phrase_id, section_id, voice_id, role, pitch, nominal_beat, nominal_dur_beats, harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, is_phrase_start/end, is_cadential, intent_tag, onset_sec, dur_sec, velocity, timing_deviation_ms, articulation, sensor_tempo_scale, sensor_amp_scale, sensor_brightness, rule_stack (list[str]), seed_path (tuple[int, ...])<br/>- score-level fields are immutable after render stage<br/>- dataclass is JSON-serializable and round-trips through OSC bundle encoding<br/>- unit tests verify field presence, immutability of score-level fields, and serialization round-trip |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-002 | Implement PerformanceIntent per-phrase metadata with arc shape, deviation bounds, tension target, restraint, and call/response role. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines PerformanceIntent(phrase_id, arc_shape, arc_peak_position, tempo_deviation_pct, dynamic_range_db, articulation_mean, breath_after_ms, tension_target, restraint, call_response_role)<br/>- arc_shape is one of parabolic/cosine/bezier/flat/inverted<br/>- conservative defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, dynamic_range_db=9, arc_peak_position=0.6, breath_after_ms=250, restraint=0.0<br/>- tests verify defaults match research-calibrated KTH k=1 values and reject out-of-range inputs |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-003 | Implement SectionEnvelope with breakpoint functions over tempo_base, density_target, dynamic_plane, brightness, tension_trajectory. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines SectionEnvelope with breakpoint-function interpolation (linear default, optional spline)<br/>- envelope samples at arbitrary normalized position 0..1 within section<br/>- phrase-arc rules compose multiplicatively with section-envelope samples<br/>- tests verify interpolation, composition with phrase arcs, and parameter bounds |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-004 | Define IntentTag enum (build/settle/question/answer/withhold/punctuate) and require every phrase to carry one. | MUST | T1 | - IntentTag enum exists in `render/events.py` with exactly six values<br/>- composition gate rejects phrases missing intent_tag on long pieces<br/>- micro pieces may use punctuate as the default<br/>- tests verify enum completeness and gate rejection path |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-005 | Define Role enum (ostinato/melody/pad/perc/accent/silence) with grid_locked flag and role-filter policy used by all rules. | MUST | T1 | - Role enum exists with grid_locked boolean attribute (ostinato=True, perc=True, melody=False, pad=False, accent=False, silence=N/A)<br/>- every rule in the stack respects a shared `rule.applies_to(role)` filter so grid-locked voices skip R1–R8<br/>- tests verify grid-locked voices emerge from the render pass with timing_deviation_ms == 0 and no microtiming jitter |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-006 | Implement seeded-RNG architecture with per-stage sub-seeds derived from a root seed along a seed_path tuple. | MUST | T1 | - `render/seed.py` exposes derive_seed(root_seed, path_tuple) returning deterministic 32-bit sub-seed<br/>- Event.seed_path records the exact path used so any randomness inside rules can be reproduced<br/>- tests verify same (root, path) always yields same sub-seed across process restarts and Python minor versions |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-007 | Refactor composition stage to emit score-tree with PerformanceIntent + SectionEnvelope + IntentTag metadata, deterministic from composition seed. | MUST | T1 | - `recursive_composer.py` and `score_tree.py` extended to attach PerformanceIntent to every phrase node and SectionEnvelope to every section node<br/>- composer accepts an explicit composition_seed argument and produces byte-identical score trees for the same seed + brief<br/>- existing pieces still compose successfully; gate passes on unchanged repertoire<br/>- tests verify determinism (two runs same seed → equal score-tree hash) and metadata presence |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-008 | Define the OSC/SuperCollider event contract that carries full Event metadata including rule_stack provenance through to the synth. | MUST | T1 | - OSC bundle schema documented in `my-claw/docs/render-osc-schema.md`<br/>- `music_tracker_runtime.py` serializes Event fields into Pbind-compatible dictionaries preserving rule_stack and seed_path<br/>- synth side (reference SC file under `my-claw/supercollider/render_contract.scd`) demonstrates reading and ignoring unknown keys gracefully<br/>- tests verify round-trip of a sample phrase through serialize → parse preserves all fields |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-009 | Build a deterministic replay harness that reproduces any past performance from (score, composition_seed, interpretation_seed, delta_track). | MUST | T1 | - `render/replay.py` exposes replay(score, seeds, delta_track) returning PerformedPart byte-identical to original<br/>- de\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+      '    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n' +\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+      '    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"details\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n' +\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+      '      {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n' +\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+      '        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type.googleapis.c